docs.lead_paragraph: A 14-year-old girl gave birth to a full-term baby in a bathroom at her Houston-area junior high school, then tried to flush it down the toilet, killing the infant, the police said. The incident at Cedar Bayou Junior High in Baytown came just three days after another 14-year-old girl delivered a stillborn fetus in the lavatory of an airplane on her way back to Houston from a middle-school field trip. The Harris County district attorney’s office decided not to pursue charges against the girl on the airplane.

docs.lead_paragraph: A 14-year-old girl on a return flight from a middle-school trip delivered a stillborn fetus in the lavatory of an airplane and disposed of it in a waste bin, the police said. The girl, whom the police did not identify, said she did not know she had been pregnant. Preliminary autopsy results indicated the fetus was stillborn, the police said. They were called to Bush Intercontinental Airport after a cleaning crew found the fetus about 15 minutes after the Continental Airlines plane landed after a flight from La Guardia Airport in New York.
